The paper proposes a technique for improving system throughput in coordinated multi-point transmission (CoMP) systems, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The proposed technique involves collaboration between multiple base stations, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the use of stochastic geometry to model the scenario, which is a topic related to multimedia (cs.MM) and communication (cs.COM).
